                            <comment id="17136272" author="rarokni@gmail.com" created="Tue, 16 Jun 2020 03:58:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=alexvanboxel&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;alexvanboxel&quot;&gt;alexvanboxel&lt;/a&gt;&#160;, bit of a corner use case.. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&#160;PS really like the utility , about to use it in a timeseries library , thanx!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17148233" author="rarokni@gmail.com" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2020 00:55:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Speaking to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=reuvenlax&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;reuvenlax&quot;&gt;reuvenlax&lt;/a&gt;&#160;issue is with any PoJO not just Proto, changing title. This is essentially not supported for now... But we should add a decent error message.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17148768" author="bhulette" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2020 15:20:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think there are two actions here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add support for recursive Beam schemas (this is a large issue, there may already be a Jira for it, or there should be)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fail early with a better error message. I think that should be the action for this ticket&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17148777" author="bhulette" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2020 15:34:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Couldn&apos;t find an existing Jira for recursive schema support so I filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-10388&quot; title=&quot;Add support for self-referential Beam schemas&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BEAM-10388&quot;&gt;BEAM-10388&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17149587" author="altay" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2020 17:33:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;/cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tysonjh&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tysonjh&quot;&gt;tysonjh&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kenn&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kenn&quot;&gt;kenn&lt;/a&gt; - For adding a proper error when a recursive schema or a recursive POJO is used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
